游릴 Problem
You need to simulate an undo operation in a text editor by reversing a sentence.
A stack is perfect here because it returns characters in the opposite order they were added.

游릴 Approach:
1. Reads a sentence.
2. Pushes each character onto a stack.
3. Pops characters to print the reversed sentence.


游릴 Sample Input
Welcome to the coding world

游릴 Sample Output
dlrow gnidoc eht ot emocleW


游릴 Solution (Stack using Linked List)

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    static class Node {
        char data;
        Node next;

        Node(char data) {
            this.data = data;
            this.next = null;
        }
    }

    static class Stack {
        Node top = null;

        void push(char data) {
            Node newnode = new Node(data);
            newnode.next = top;
            top = newnode;
        }

        char pop() {
            char val = top.data;
            top = top.next;
            return val;
        }

        boolean empty() {
            return top == null;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String s = sc.nextLine();

        Stack stack = new Stack();

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            stack.push(s.charAt(i));
        }

        while (!stack.empty()) {
            System.out.print(stack.pop());
        }
    }
}

游릴 Time Complexity - O(n) [pushing n characters + popping n characters]
游릴 Space Complexity - O(n)  [stack holds all characters]



游릴 Solution (USING INBUILT STACK):

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {
    public static void main(String[] args) 
    {
       Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
        String s= sc.nextLine();
        
        Stack<Character> stack=new Stack<>();
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++)    // push logic
        {
         stack.push(s.charAt(i));
        }
        
        while(stack.empty()!=true)  //pop logic
        {
            System.out.print(stack.pop());
        }
        
    }
}
